ty) | 4.1.60.Final | 100% (0/0 calls) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Netty Handler Proxy adds client-side support for connecting through proxy protocols such as SOCKS and HTTP CONNECT tunneling. It provides proxy channel handlers and connection events that integrate with Netty's asynchronous networking pipeline.</details> |\n./skills/README.md:44:### `close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs`\n./skills/README.md:46:Closes batches of open pull requests that have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI.\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:154:  posts a human-intervention comment. Also runs the PR review queues.\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:330:        Disp->>GH: Push preserve branch + human-intervention comment\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:191:shared repository file changed, the PR must be labeled `human-intervention`\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:2:name: close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:3:description: Close batches of graalvm-reachability-metadata pull requests that either have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI, and revert their linked issues by clearing assignees and moving project status to `Todo`.\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:6:# Close Human-Intervention and Failing-CI PRs\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:18:- The PR has the `human-intervention` label.\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:29:   - Fetch open human-intervention PRs:\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:31:     gh pr list -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --state open --label human-intervention --limit 200 --json number,title,url,labels,statusCheckRollup\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:150:     gh pr close PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --comment \"Closing this human-intervention PR and returning the linked issue to Todo.\"\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:183:- PRs closed for `human-intervention`\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:23:HUMAN_INTERVENTION_LABEL = \"human-intervention\"\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:59:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", labels)\n./forge/do_up_to_date_work.sh:93:      Process up to N fails-native-image-run tasks per run; 0 disables it. Defaults to\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:89:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", create_call)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:105:| `fails-native-image-run` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed while running the native image. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:109:| `fixes-native-image-run-fail` | PR | PR repairs a `fails-native-image-run` compatibility issue. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:114:| `human-intervention` | Issue / PR | Automation could not safely complete the work without manual follow-up, or automated PR review requested changes. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:115:| `human-intervention-fixed` | PR | Manual follow-up has fixed a PR previously requiring intervention; review automation may approve and merge it after merge gates pass. |\n./metadata/io.netty/netty-handler-proxy/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/netty/netty-handler-proxy/4.1.60.Final/netty-handler-proxy-4.1.60.Final-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/io.netty/netty-handler-proxy/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/netty/netty-handler-proxy/4.1.60.Final/netty-handler-proxy-4.1.60.Final-test-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/io.netty/netty-handler-proxy/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/netty/netty-handler-proxy/4.1.60.Final/netty-handler-proxy-4.1.60.Final-javadoc.jar\",\n./stats/io.netty/netty-handler-proxy/4.1.60.Final/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"io.netty:netty-handler-proxy:4.1.60.Final\",\n./stats/io.